result.execSummary:
The defendant Shanice L Sims was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Restitution in the amount of $671.74 ordered payable to Jajuan M. L. received, signed, and filed with court.
Attorney Robert E Webb in court.  Megan Patricia Carmody appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Parties will stipulate to restitution owed.  State to provide stipulation and order.
Added consecutive to any other sentence

Defendant Shanice L Sims in court with attorney Robert E Webb.  Francesco Mineo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant changes plea to GUILTY to the amended charges.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the amended information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.

AS TO COUNT 1:

The Court sentenced defendant to serve 5  MONTHS in the House of Corrections, consecutive to COUNT 2 and any other sentence, with Huber release privileges for work; credit for 2 days time served.   Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 15 MONTHS with the following conditions:
-Restitution set at $1,336.00 payable to Jajuan L.  Restitution to Nkrumah D. to be determined, are to be collected during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment.  Restitution to be paid before any court costs, fees and assessments
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments are to be collected during term of probation;  nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge to be collected during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-No association with drug users, drug dealers and drug houses or otherwise engage in drug dealing
-Cooperate with agent
-Obtain/maintain employment unless in school.  If in school full-time, defendant to have a part-time job 
-Obtain GED or HSED
-Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification Program
-No contact with Jajuan L. and Nkrumah D. 
-Court allows for expungement if all terms of probation are completed.

AS TO COUNT 2:
The Court sentenced defendant to serve 60 DAYS in the House of Corrections, consecutive to COUNT 1 and any other sentence, with Huber release privileges for work;  Court STAYED sentence and placed the defendant on PROBATION for a period of 15 MONTHS with the following conditions:
-Defendant to pay Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments are to be collected during term of probation;  nonpayment penalty shall be a civil judgment
-Defendant is to provide a DNA sample and pay the related surcharge to be collected during term of probation; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause
-No association with drug users, drug dealers and drug houses or otherwise engage in drug dealing
-Cooperate with agent
-Obtain/maintain employment unless in school.  If in school full-time, defendant to have a part-time job 
-Obtain GED or HSED
-Successfully complete a Cognitive Thinking Behavioral Modification Program
-No contact with Jajuan L. and Nkrumah D. 
-Court allows for expungement if all terms of probation are completed.
